      "stem_html": "<p>The amino acid phenylalanine has p<i>K</i><sub>a</sub> = 1.83, and tryptophan has p<i>K</i><sub>a</sub> = 2.83. Which is the stronger acid?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBazhRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--838f252fc1aa6c5de2820f7b8eaf855feed930cd/OChem_02_08_003.jpg\" alt=\"Structures of the amino acids phenylalanine and tryptophan. Both have carboxylic acid groups, alpha amino groups, and aryl groups. Tryptophan has nitrogen in ring system.\">",
